ws standard conventions and doesn't need reporting. I'm checking if there are any other discrepancies in how the source data was translated. I see the knowledge file condensed the mobile phone field description by merging the base requirement with the conditional note, effectively removing the standalone \"必須\" marker from the base description. While this might have been an attempt to clarify the conditional nature of the requirement, it does technically alter the source information. That's the only issue I'm flagging—a minor omission.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":20649,"cache_read_input_tokens":29873,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":20649,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":8},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"87731e93-508e-4331-96c6-cbb37abd3bdc","uuid":"2396f894-2054-4420-9ed1-f89ba1efc908"}
